29  import java.nio.charset.Charset;
30  import java.nio.charset.CharsetDecoder;
31  import java.nio.charset.CharsetEncoder;
32  import sun.nio.cs.HistoricallyNamedCharset;
33  
34  public class MS950_OLD
35      extends Charset
36      implements HistoricallyNamedCharset
37  {
38  
39      public MS950_OLD() {
40          super("x-windows-950-OLD", null);
41      }
42  
43      public String historicalName() {
44          return "MS950";
45      }
46  
47      public boolean contains(Charset cs) {
48          return ((cs.name().equals("US-ASCII"))
49                  || (cs instanceof MS950_OLD));
50      }
51  
52      public CharsetDecoder newDecoder() {
53          return new Decoder(this);
54      }
55  
56      public CharsetEncoder newEncoder() {
57          return new Encoder(this);
58      }
59  
60  
61      /**
62       * These accessors are temporarily supplied while sun.io
63       * converters co-exist with the sun.nio.cs.{ext} charset coders
64       * These facilitate sharing of conversion tables between the
65       * two co-existing implementations. When sun.io converters
66       * are made extinct these will be unncessary and should be removed
67       */
68  
69      public short[] getDecoderIndex1() {
70          return Decoder.index1;
71      }
72  
73      public String[] getDecoderIndex2() {
74          return Decoder.index2;
75      }
76  
77      public short[] getEncoderIndex1() {
78          return Encoder.index1;
79      }
80  
81      public String[] getEncoderIndex2() {
82          return Encoder.index2;
83      }
